cs.CC, cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.SC, cs.AG. 

The paper deals with complexity and algebraic geometry, suggesting that it could belong to cs.CC (computational complexity), cs.CG (computational geometry), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.SC (symbolic computation), or cs.AG (algebraic geometry). The focus on constructing a hitting set for the closure of VP, a class of polynomials that can be approximated by small algebraic circuits, suggests that cs.CC and cs.SC are the most likely categories. The use of anti-concentration results for polynomials and the existential theory of the reals also suggests cs.SC and cs.CC. The mention of the Noether Normalization Lemma suggests cs.AG as a possible category. Finally, the use of basic tools from algebraic geometry suggests cs.AG and cs.CG as possible categories.
